Sentencas: La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 perovskite, characterized with high conductivity and temperature resistance, is potentialmaterial for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) interconnects or interconnect coating.
Titulo: Preparing La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 conductive perovskite via optimal processes: High-energy ball milling and calcinations

Sentencas: Preparation processes of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 were optimized via high-energy ball milling (HEBM) and calcinations in order to synthesize efficiently a specimen with low electrical resistivity.
Titulo: Preparing La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 conductive perovskite via optimal processes: High-energy ball milling and calcinations

Sentencas: The optimal process conditions were determined to be an HEBM time of 3 h, sintering temperature of 1200 degrees C, sintering time of 15 h and triple cycle.
Titulo: Preparing La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 conductive perovskite via optimal processes: High-energy ball milling and calcinations

Sentencas: The lowest resistivity generated by the optimized process was 0.0039 Omega m, namely 0.10 Omega in the form of bulk electrical resistance.
Titulo: Preparing La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 conductive perovskite via optimal processes: High-energy ball milling and calcinations

Sentencas: To summarize, La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 perovskite characterized by low resistivity was produced with high preparation efficiency through the optimal process.
Titulo: Preparing La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 conductive perovskite via optimal processes: High-energy ball milling and calcinations
